## Architecture

Hexagonal (Ports & Adapters) — dependency direction is strictly inward:

```
transport/ → infrastructure/ → application/ → domain/
```

| Layer | Location | Purpose |
|-------|----------|---------|
| Domain | `src/domain/` | Business rules, entities, value objects, repository interfaces |
| Application | `src/application/` | Use cases — orchestrate domain objects |
| Infrastructure | `src/infrastructure/` | Adapters — database, HTTP clients, cache, queues |
| Transport | `src/transport/` | Entry points — HTTP server, Kafka consumer, CLI |

## Getting Started

```bash
npm install
npm run dev       # start in watch mode
npm run build     # compile TypeScript
npm test          # run tests
npm run typecheck # type-check without emitting
npm run lint      # lint source files
```

